Septic tank outfalls and domestic misconnections could be an easy fix for @EnvAgencyNW to improve water quality. The river below this domestic pipe is utterly devoid of life. 
Why cant the river regulator regulate things like this?
@RiverActionUK @Feargal_Sharkey @UnderwaterMedia https://t.co/fjksfXsWwc

@HannaMuses @River_Douglas_ @EnvAgencyNW @RiverActionUK @Feargal_Sharkey @UnderwaterMedia @UKWater @UKEnvironment @EnvAgency This is self regulation of a septic tank in action.
Doesn't discharge into a running watercourse, doesn't have a proper drainage field of infiltration pipes either.
Sludge is simply being deposited onto the surface of what should be a dry ditch which would normally be grazed. https://t.co/CsvCpRpIcI

@HannaMuses @River_Douglas_ @EnvAgencyNW @RiverActionUK @Feargal_Sharkey @UnderwaterMedia @UKWater @UKEnvironment Self regulation isn't happening.
Any oversight would be something as that certainly isn't happening by the @EnvAgency currently.
Many septic tanks that discharge to watercourses haven't been upragaded and many owners have no intention of doing so.

